# file CIRA-86_mid_2.7km.amc - mid-latitude profile, starting from 2.7 km
# altitude for comparison with the O2 zenith absorption data in Reber,
# JGR 77_3831 (July 1972).  The paper does not give surface pressure
# measurements, but states that the measurements at altitude were made during
# the summer.  So, the P,T profile here is from the CIRA-86 table for July
# at 35 deg. N latitude, with the base pressure and temperature interpolated
# to 2700 m.
#
f 40 GHz  80 GHz  2.0 MHz
output f GHz  tau dB
za 0 deg
tol 0

T0 2.7 K
#
# Layer pressures and temperatures here are interpolated from the CIRA-86
# reference atmosphere for July, for 35 deg N latitude.
#
# Reference:
#
#   Committee on Space Research (COSPAR). The COSPAR International Atmosphere
#   (CIRA-86), [Internet]. NCAS British Atmospheric Data Centre, 2006-2011.
#   Available from
#     http://badc.nerc.ac.uk/view/badc.nerc.ac.uk__ATOM__dataent_CIRA .
#
layer
Pbase  0 mbar  # z = 0.00 km
Tbase  219.224 K

layer
Pbase 37.200 mbar  # z = 22.82 km
Tbase 219.224 K
column dry_air vmr

